Refer to http://www.ibiblio.org/apollo/index.html for more information.

000002,000002:                                                                                          	# Copyright:    Public domain.
000003,000003:                                                                                          	# Filename:     MAIN.agc
000004,000004:                                                                                          	# Purpose:      Part of the source code for Aurora (revision 12),
000005,000005:                                                                                          	# Assembler:    yaYUL
000006,000006:                                                                                          	# Contact:      Ron Burkey <info@sandroid.org>.
000007,000007:                                                                                          	# Website:      https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo/index.html
000008,000008:                                                                                          	# Page scans:   https://archive.org/details/aurora00dapg
000009,000009:                                                                                          	# Mod history:  2016-09-20 JL   Created.
000010,000010:                                                                                          	#               
000011,000011:                                                                                          	# MAIN.agc is a little different from the other Aurora12 files  
000012,000012:                                                                                          	# provided, in that it doesn't represent anything that appears 
000013,000013:                                                                                          	# directly in the original source.  What we have done for 
000014,000014:                                                                                          	# organizational purposes is to split the huge monolithic source 
000015,000015:                                                                                          	# code into smaller, more manageable chunks--i.e., into individual
000016,000016:                                                                                          	# source files.  Those files are rejoined within this file as 
000017,000017:                                                                                          	# "includes".  It just makes it a little easier to work with.  The
000018,000018:                                                                                          	# code chunks correspond to natural divisions into sub-programs.  
000019,000019:                                                                                          	# The divisions are by the assembly listing itself.
000020,000020: 
000021,000021:                                                                                          	# Source file name                                Starting Page
000022,000022:                                                                                          	# ----------------                                -------------
000023,000023: 
000024,000024: $ASSEMBLY_AND_OPERATION_INFORMATION.agc		# 1
000026,000002:                                                                                          	# Copyright:    Public domain.

000028,000004:                                                                                          	# Purpose:      Part of the source code for Aurora (revision 12).

000055,000031:                                                                                          	# VERB INFORMATION.
000056,000032: 
000057,000033:                                                                                          	#  REGULAR VERBS
000058,000034:                                                                                          	# 01  DISPLAY OCTAL COMP 1 (R1)
000059,000035:                                                                                          	# 02  DISPLAY OCTAL COMP 2 (R1)
000060,000036:                                                                                          	# 03  DISPLAY OCTAL COMP 3 (R1)
000061,000037:                                                                                          	# 04  DISPLAY OCTAL COMP 1,2 (R1,R2)
000062,000038:                                                                                          	# 05  DISPLAY OCTAL COMP 1,2,3 (R1,R2,R3)
000063,000039:                                                                                          	# 06  DECIMAL DISPLAY
000064,000040:                                                                                          	# 07  DP DECIMAL DISPLAY (R1,R2)
000065,000041:                                                                                          	# 10  SPARE
000066,000042:                                                                                          	# 11  MONITOR OCT COMP 1 (R1)
000067,000043:                                                                                          	# 12  MONITOR OCT COMP 2 (R1)
000068,000044:                                                                                          	# 13  MONITOR OCT COMP 3 (R1)
000069,000045:                                                                                          	# 14  MONITOR OCT COMP 1,2 (R1)
000070,000046:                                                                                          	# 15  MONITOR OCT COMP 1,2,3 (R1,R2,R3)
000071,000047:                                                                                          	# 16  MONITOR DECIMAL
000072,000048:                                                                                          	# 17  MONITOR DP DECIMAL (R1,R2)
000073,000049:                                                                                          	# 20  SPARE
000074,000050:                                                                                          	# 21  LOAD COMP 1 (R1)
000075,000051:                                                                                          	# 22  LOAD COMP 2 (R2)
000076,000052:                                                                                          	# 23  LOAD COMP 3 (R3)
000077,000053:                                                                                          	# 24  LOAD COMP 1,2 (R1,R2)
000078,000054:                                                                                          	# 25  LOAD COMP 1,2,3 (R1,R2,R3)
000079,000055:                                                                                          	# 26  SPARE
000080,000056:                                                                                          	# 27  FIXED MEMORY DISPLAY 
000081,000057:                                                                                          	# 30  REQUEST EXECUTIVE
000082,000058:                                                                                          	# 31  REQUEST WAITLIST
000083,000059:                                                                                          	# 32  C(R2) INTO R3, C(R1) INTO R2
000084,000060:                                                                                          	# 33  PROCEED WITHOUT DATA
000085,000061:                                                                                          	# 34  TERMINATE CURRENT TEST OR LOAD REQUEST
000086,000062:                                                                                          	# 35  TEST LIGHTS
000087,000063:                                                                                          	# 36  FRESH START
000088,000064:                                                                                          	# 37  CHANGE MAJOR MODE
000089,000065:                                                                                          	# END OF REGULAR VERBS
000090,000066: 
000091,000067:                                                                                          	# EXTENDED VERBS
000092,000068:                                                                                          	# 40  ZERO (USED WITH NOUNS 20, 40, AND 70)
000093,000069:                                                                                          	# 41  COARSE ALIGN (USED WITH NOUNS 20, 40, AND 70)
000094,000070:                                                                                          	# 42  FINE ALIGN IMU
000095,000071:                                                                                          	# 43  LOAD IMU ATTITUDE ERROR METERS
000096,000072:                                                                                          	# 44  ILLEGAL VERB
000097,000073:                                                                                          	# 45  COMMAND LR TO POSITION 2
000098,000074:                                                                                          	# 46  SAMPLE RADAR DATA ONCE PER SECOND
000099,000075:                                                                                          	# 47  PERFORM LEM FCS TEST
000100,000076:                                                                                          	# 50  PLEASE PERFORM
000102,000078:                                                                                          	# 51  PLEASE MARK
000103,000079:                                                                                          	# 52  PLEASE MARK Y
000104,000080:                                                                                          	# 53  PLEASE MARK X OR Y
000105,000081:                                                                                          	# 54  PULSE TORQUE GYROS
000106,000082:                                                                                          	# 55  ALIGN TIME
000107,000083:                                                                                          	# 56  PERFORM BANKSUM
000108,000084:                                                                                          	# 57  PERFORM SYSTEM TEST
000109,000085:                                                                                          	# 60  ILLEGAL VERB
000110,000086:                                                                                          	# 61  ILLEGAL VERB
000111,000087:                                                                                          	# 62  SCAN LEM INBITS
000112,000088:                                                                                          	# 63  INITIALIZE AGS
000113,000089:                                                                                          	# 64  ILLEGAL VERB

000115,000091:                                                                                          	# 66  ILLEGAL VERB
000116,000092:                                                                                          	# 67  ILLEGAL VERB
000117,000093:                                                                                          	# 70  ILLEGAL VERB

000389,000031:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING ROUTINE CAN BE USED TO CALL A SUBROUTINE IN ANOTHER BANK. IN THE BANKCALL VERSION, THE
000390,000032:                                                                                          	# CADR OF THE SUBROUTINE IMMEDIATELY FOLLOWS THE TC BANKCALL INSTRUCTION, WITH C(A) AND C(L) PRESERVED.
000391,000033: 
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:34: Fatal Error: Symbol "ENDINTFF" undefined or offset bad
000392,000034: ???????                                           SETLOC   ENDINTFF                      	#

000393,000035: ???????           52000        BANKCALL           DXCH     BUF2                          	# SAVE INCOMING A,L.
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:36: Fatal Error: Symbol "Q" undefined or offset bad
000394,000036: ???????           50000                           INDEX    Q                             	# PICK UP CADR.
000395,000037: ???????           30000                           CA       0                             	#
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:38: Fatal Error: Symbol "Q" undefined or offset bad
000396,000038: ???????           24000                           INCR     Q                             	# SO WE RETURN TO THE LOC. AFTER THE CADR.
000397,000039: 
000398,000040:                                                                                          	# SWCALL IS IDENTICAL TO BANKCALL, EXCEPT THAT THE CADR ARRIVES IN A.
000399,000041:

000400,000042: ???????           54000        SWCALL             TS       L                             	#
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:43: Fatal Error: Symbol "FBANK" undefined or offset bad
000401,000043: ???????           22000                           LXCH     FBANK                         	# SWITCH BANKS, SAVING RETURN.
000402,000044: ???????           76426                           MASK     LOW10                         	# GET SUB-ADDRESS OF CADR.
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:45: Fatal Error: Symbol "Q" undefined or offset bad
000403,000045: ???????           56000                           XCH      Q                             	# A,L NOW CONTAINS DP RETURN.
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:46: Fatal Error: Symbol "BUF2" undefined or offset bad
000404,000046: ???????           52000                           DXCH     BUF2                          	# RESTORING INPUTS IF THIS IS A BANKCALL.
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:47: Fatal Error: Symbol "Q" undefined or offset bad
000405,000047: ???????           50000                           INDEX    Q                             	#

000407,000049:

000408,000050: ???????           56000        SWRETURN           XCH      BUF2       +1                 	# COMES HERE TO RETURN TO CALLER. C(A,L)

000409,000051: ???????           56000                           XCH      FBANK                         	# ARE PRESERVED FOR RETURN.

000410,000052: ???????           56000                           XCH      BUF2       +1                 	#

000414,000056:                                                                                          	# FOLLOWING THE TC POSTJUMP INSTRUCTION.

000451,000093: 
000453,000095:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING SUBROUTINES PROVIDE TO THE BASIC PROGRAMMER ENTRY INTO AND RETURN FROM ANY INTERPRETIVE
000454,000096:                                                                                          	# CODING WHICH DOES NOT USE THE ENTERING CONTENTS OF Q AND WHICH RETURNS VIA DANZIG. C(A) AND C(L) ARE SAVED.
000455,000097: 
000456,000098:                                                                                          	# USER'S RESPONSIBILITY TO FILL IN ADVANCE THE APPROPRIATE OPERAND AND ADDRESS REGISTERS USED BY THE
000457,000099:                                                                                          	# INTERPRETIVE CODING SUCH AS MPAC, BUF, ADDRWD, ETC.; AND TO CONFIRM THAT THE INTERPRETIVE CODING MEETS THE
000458,000100:                                                                                          	# ABOVE RESTRICTIONS WITH RESPECT TO Q AND DANZIG.
000459,000101: 
000460,000102:                                                                                          	# USEPRET AND USPRCADR MUST NOT BE USED IN INTERRUPT.
000461,000103: 
000462,000104:                                                                                          	# 1. USEPRET ACCESSES INTERPRETIVE CODING WHICH CAN BE ENTERED WITHOUT CHANGING FBANK.
000463,000105:                                                                                          	#    THE CALLING SEQUENCE IS AS FOLLOWS:
000464,000106: 
000465,000107:                                                                                          	# L             TC              USEPRET
000466,000108:                                                                                          	# L+1           TC,TCF          INTPRETX                        TC,TCF MEANS TC OR TCF
000467,000109:                                                                                          	#                                                               INTPRETX IS THE INTERPRETIVE CODING
000468,000110:                                                                                          	#                                                               RETURN IS TO L+2
000469,000111: 
000470,000112:                                                                                          	# 2. USPRCADR ACCESSES INTERPRETIVE CODING IN OTHER THAN THE USER'S FBANK. THE CALLING SEQUENCE IS AS FOLLOWS:
000471,000113: 
000472,000114:                                                                                          	# L             TC              USPRCADR
000473,000115:                                                                                          	# L+1           CADR            INTPRETX                        INTPRETX IS THE INTERPRETIVE CODING
000474,000116:                                                                                          	#                                                               RETURN IS TO L+2
000475,000117: 
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:118: Fatal Error: Symbol "Q" undefined or offset bad
000476,000118: ???????           56000        USEPRET            XCH      Q                             	# FETCH Q, SAVING A
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:119: Fatal Error: Symbol "LOC" undefined or offset bad
000477,000119: ???????           54000                           TS       LOC                           	# L+1 TO LOC
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:120: Fatal Error: Symbol "FBANK" undefined or offset bad
000478,000120: ???????           30000                           CA       FBANK                         	#
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:121: Fatal Error: Symbol "BANKSET" undefined or offset bad
000479,000121: ???????           54000                           TS       BANKSET                       	# USERS BANK TO BANKSET
000480,000122: ???????           37650                           CA       BIT8                          	#
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:123: Fatal Error: Symbol "EDOP" undefined or offset bad
000481,000123: ???????           54000                           TS       EDOP                          	# EXIT INSTRUCTION TO EDOP
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:124: Fatal Error: Symbol "Q" undefined or offset bad
000482,000124: ???????           30000                           CA       Q                             	# RETRIEVE ORIGINAL A
INTER-BANK_COMMUNICATION.agc:125: Fatal Error: Symbol "LOC" undefined or offset bad
000483,000125: ???????           00000                           TC       LOC                           	#
000484,000126:

000485,000127: ???????           54000        USPRCADR           TS       LOC                           	# SAVE A

000527,000169: 
000528,000170:                                                                                          	# T6JOBCHK DETERMINES IF T6 = -0 ( A T6RUPT HAS OCCURRED ) OR IF T6
000529,000171:                                                                                          	# EQUALS +0 ( T6 NOT COUNTING DOWN ) OR =SOME POS.OR NEG. NUMBER ( T6
000530,000172:                                                                                          	# BEING DECREMENTED AND NO RUPT IS NEEDED ).

000582,000019:                                                                                          	#       NOV 10, 1966
000583,000020:

000585,000022:                                                                                          	#       date of the program revision or the assembly.]
000586,000023:

000588,000025:                                                                                          	# reduction in image quality) are available online at

000593,000030: 
000595,000032:                                                                                          	# SECTION 1:  DISPATCHER
000596,000033: 
000597,000034:                                                                                          	#          ENTRY TO THE INTERPRETER. INTPRET SETS LOC TO THE FIRST INSTRUCTION, BANKSET TO THE FBANK OF THE
000598,000035:                                                                                          	# OBJECT INTERPRETIVE PROGRAM, AND INTBIT15 TO THE BIT15 CONTENTS OF FBANK. INTERPRETIVE PROGRAMS MAY BE IN
000599,000036:                                                                                          	# VIRTUALLY ALL BANKS PRESENT UNDER ANY SUPER-BANK SETTING, WITH THE RESTRICTION THAT PROGRAMS IN HIGH BANKS
000600,000037:                                                                                          	# (BIT15 OF FBANK = 1) DO NOT REFER TO LOWBANKS, AND VICE-VERSA. THE INTERPRETER DOES NOT SWITCH SUPER-BANK,
000601,000038:                                                                                          	# NOR DOES IT SWITCH EBANKS. MOST EBANK SWITCHING IS DONE BY THE EXECUTIVE PROGRAM.
000602,000039: 
000603,000040:    6000                                           SETLOC   6000                          	#
000604,000041: 
000605,000042:    6000           00006        INTPRET            EXTEND                                 	# SET LOC TO THE WORD FOLLOWING THE TC.
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:43: Fatal Error: Symbol "LOC" undefined or offset bad
000606,000043:    6001           22000                           QXCH     LOC                           	#
000607,000044: 
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:45: Fatal Error: Symbol "FBANK" undefined or offset bad
000608,000045:    6002           30000                 +2        CA       FBANK                         	# INTERPRETIVE BRANCHES FINISH HERE.
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:46: Fatal Error: Symbol "BANKSET" undefined or offset bad
000609,000046:    6003           54000                           TS       BANKSET                       	#
000610,000047:    6004           77641                           MASK     BIT15                         	# GET 15TH BIT FOR INDEXABLE ADDRESSES.

000611,000048:    6005           54000                           TS       INTBIT15                      	#
000612,000049:    6006           66426                           AD       LOW10                         	# THIS VERSION IS USED IN PROCESSING

000613,000050:    6007           54000                           TS       INTB15+                       	# INDEXABLE FIXED-BANK ADDRESSES.
000614,000051: 
000615,000052:    6010           16023                           TCF      NEWOPS                        	# PICK UP OP CODE PAIR AND BEGIN.
000616,000053:

000618,000055:    6012           16003                           TCF      INTPRET    +3                 	# (ACTUALLY PART OF THE EXECUTIVE).
000619,000056:

000628,000065:    6017           16032                           TCF      OPJUMP                        	# THE LAST PAIR RETRIEVED. IF SO, EXECUTE.

000632,000069:    6021           16000                           TCF      CHANG2                        	# PRESENT, AND IF SO, CHANGE JOBS.
000633,000070:

000664,000101: 
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:102: Fatal Error: Symbol "LOC" undefined or offset bad
000665,000102:    6046           24000                           INCR     LOC                           	# IF SO, TO SHOW WE PICKED UP A WORD.
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:103: Fatal Error: Symbol "ADDRWD" undefined or offset bad
000666,000103:    6047           54000                           TS       ADDRWD                        	#
000667,000104: 
000669,000106:                                                                                          	#          FINAL DIGESTION OF DIRECT ADDRESSES OF OP CODES WITH 01 PREFIX IS DONE HERE. IN EACH CASE, THE
000670,000107:                                                                                          	# REQUIRED 12-BIT SUB-ADDRESS IS LEFT IN ADDRWD, WITH ANY REQUIRED BANK SWITCHING DONE (F ONLY). ADDRESSES LESS
000671,000108:                                                                                          	# THAN 45D ARE TAKEN TO BE RELATIVE TO THE WORK AREA. THE OP CODE IS NOW IN BITS 1-5 OF CYR WITH BIT 14 = 1.
000672,000109: 
000673,000110: 
000674,000111: 
000675,000112:    6050           66171                           AD       -ENDVAC                       	# SEE IF ADDRESS RELATIVE TO WORK AREA.

000689,000126:    6063           54000                 +1        TS       FBANK                         	# SWITCH BANKS AND LEAVE SUB-ADDRESS IN
000690,000127:    6064           76426                           MASK     LOW10                         	# ADDRWD FOR OPERAND RETRIEVAL.
000691,000128:    6065           67645                           AD       2K                            	#

000695,000132: 
000697,000134:                                                                                          	#          THE FOLLOWING ROUTINE PROCESSES INTERPRETIVE INDEXED ADDRESSES. AN INTERPRETER INDEX REGISTER MAY
000698,000135:                                                                                          	# CONTAIN THE ADDRESS OF ANY ERASABLE REGISTER (0-42 BEING RELATIVE TO THE VAC AREA) OR ANY INTERPRETIVE PROGRAM
000699,000136:                                                                                          	# BANK, OR ANY INTEGER IN THAT RANGE.
000700,000137:

LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:177: Fatal Error: Symbol "ADDRWD" undefined or offset bad
000740,000177:    6132           26000                           ADS      ADDRWD                        	#
000741,000178: 
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:179: Fatal Error: Symbol "CYR" undefined or offset bad
000742,000179:    6133           50000        INDERASE           INDEX    CYR                           	#
000743,000180:    6134           36234                           3        INDJUMP    -1                 	#
000744,000181: 
000746,000183:                                                                                          	#          PUSH-UP ROUTINES. WHEN NO OPERAND ADDRESS IS GIVEN, THE APPROPRIATE OPERAND IS TAKEN FROM THE PUSH-DOWN
000747,000184:                                                                                          	# LIST. IN MOST CASES THE MODE OF THE RESULT (VECTOR OR SCALAR) OF THE LAST ARITHMETIC OPERATION PERFORMED
000748,000185:                                                                                          	# IS THE SAME AS THE TYPE OF OPERAND DESIRED (ALL ADD/SUBTRACT ETC.). EXCEPTIONS TO THIS GENERAL RULE ARE LISTED
000749,000186:                                                                                          	# BELOW (NOTE THAT IN EVERY CASE THE MODE REGISTER IS LEFT INTACT):
000750,000187: 
000751,000188:                                                                                          	#          1.  VXSC AND V/SC WANT THE OPPOSITE TYPE OF OPERAND, E.G., IF THE LAST OPERATION YIELDED A VECTOR
000752,000189:                                                                                          	# RESULT, VXSC WANTS A SCALAR.
000753,000190: 
000754,000191:                                                                                          	#          2.  THE LOAD CODES SHOULD LOAD THE ACCUMULATOR INDEPENDENT OF THE RESULT OF THE LAST OPERATION. THIS
000755,000192:                                                                                          	# INCLUDES VLOAD, DLOAD, TLOAD, PDDL, AND PDVL (NO PUSHUP WITH SLOAD).
000756,000193: 
000757,000194:                                                                                          	#          3.  SOME ARITHMETIC OPERATIONS REQUIRE A STANDARD TYPE OF OPERAND REGARDLESS OF THE PREVIOUS OPERATION.
000758,000195:                                                                                          	# THIS INCLUDES SIGN WANTING DP AND TAD REQUIRING TP.
000759,000196: 
000760,000197:    6135           36227        PUSHUP             CAF      OCT23                         	# IF THE LOW 5 BITS OF CYR ARE LESS THAN
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:198: Fatal Error: Symbol "CYR" undefined or offset bad
000761,000198:    6136           70000                           MASK     CYR                           	# 20, THIS OP REQUIRES SPECIAL ATTENTION.
000762,000199:    6137           66142                           AD       -OCT10                        	# (NO -0).
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:200: Fatal Error: Symbol "A" undefined or offset bad
000763,000200:    6140           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
000764,000201:    6141           16153                           TCF      REGUP                         	# FOR ALL CODES GREATEER THAN OCT 7.
000765,000202: 
000766,000203:    6142           77767        -OCT10             OCT      -10                           	#
000767,000204: 
000768,000205:    6143           66045                           AD       NEG4                          	# WE NOW HAVE 7 - OP CODE (MOD4). SEE IF
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:206: Fatal Error: Symbol "A" undefined or offset bad
000769,000206:    6144           10000                           CCS      A                             	# THE OP CODE (MOD4) IS THREE (REVERSE).
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:207: Fatal Error: Symbol "A" undefined or offset bad
000770,000207:    6145           50000                           INDEX    A                             	# NO - THE MODE IS DEFINITE.  PICK UP THE
000771,000208:    6146           46164                           CS       NO.WDS                        	#
000772,000209:    6147           16155                           TCF      REGUP      +2                 	#
000773,000210: 
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:211: Fatal Error: Symbol "MODE" undefined or offset bad
000774,000211:    6150           50000                           INDEX    MODE                          	# FOR VXSC AND V/SC WE WANT THE REQUIRED
000775,000212:    6151           46162                           CS       REVCNT                        	# PUSHLOC DECREMENT WITHOUT CHANGING THE
000776,000213:    6152           16155                           TCF      REGUP      +2                 	# MODE AT THIS TIME.
000777,000214: 
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:215: Fatal Error: Symbol "MODE" undefined or offset bad
000778,000215:    6153           50000        REGUP              INDEX    MODE                          	# MOST ALL OP CODES PUSHUP HERE.
000779,000216:    6154           46164                           CS       NO.WDS                        	#
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:217: Fatal Error: Symbol "PUSHLOC" undefined or offset bad
000780,000217:    6155           26000                 +2        ADS      PUSHLOC                       	#
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:218: Fatal Error: Symbol "ADDRWD" undefined or offset bad
000781,000218:    6156           54000                           TS       ADDRWD                        	#
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:219: Fatal Error: Symbol "CYR" undefined or offset bad
000782,000219:    6157           50000                           INDEX    CYR                           	#
000783,000220:    6160           76234                           7        INDJUMP    -1                 	# (THE INDEX MAKES THIS A TCF.)
000784,000221: 
000785,000222:    6161           00002                           OCT      2                             	# REVERSE PUSHUP DECREMENT. VECTOR TAKES 2
000786,000223:    6162           00006        REVCNT             OCT      6                             	# WORDS, SCALAR TAKES 6.
000787,000224:    6163           00006                           OCT      6                             	#
000788,000225:    6164           00002        NO.WDS             OCT      2                             	# CONVENTIONAL DECREMENT IS 6 WORDS VECTOR
000789,000226:    6165           00003                           OCT      3                             	# 2 IN DP, AND 3 IN TP.
000790,000227:    6166           00006                           OCT      6                             	#
000791,000228: 
000793,000230:                                                                                          	#          TEST THE SECOND PREFIX BIT TO SEE IF THIS IS A MISCELLANEOUS OR A UNARY/SHORT SHIFT OPERATION.
000794,000231: 
LIST_PROCESSING_INTERPRETER.agc:232: Fatal Error: Symbol "CYR" undefined or offset bad
000795,000232:    6167           10000        OPJUMP2            CCS      CYR                           	# TEST SECOND PREFIX BIT.
000796,000233:    6170           16217                           TCF      OPJUMP3                       	# TEST THIRD BIT TO SEE IF UNARY OR SHIFT
000797,000234: 
000798,000235:    6171           77722        -ENDVAC            DEC      -45        B-14               	#
000799,000236: 
000800,000237:                                                                                          	#          THE FOLLOWING ROUTINE PROCESSES ADDRESSES OF SUFFIX CLASS 10. THEY ARE BASICALLY WORK AREA ADDRESSES
000801,000238:                                                                                          	# IN THE RANGE 0 - 52, ERASABLE ADRES CONSTANTS FROM 100 - 1777, AND FCADRS ABOVE THAT. ALL 15 BITS ARE AVAILABLE
000802,000239:                                                                                          	# IN CONTRAST TO SUFFIX 1, IN WHICH ONLY THE LOW ORDER 14 ARE AVAILABLE.

000933,000370: 
000935,000372:                                                                                          	# SECTION 2  LOAD AND STORE PACKAGE.
000936,000373: 
000937,000374:                                                                                          	#          A SET OF SIXTEEN STORE CODES ARE PROVIDED AS THE PRIMARY METHOD OF STORING THE MULTI-PURPOSE
000938,000375:                                                                                          	# ACCUMULATOR (MPAC). IF IN THE DANZIG SECTION LOC REFERS TO AN ALGEBRAICALLY POSITIVE WORD, IT IS TAKEN AS A
000939,000376:                                                                                          	# STORE CODE WITH A CORRESPONDING ERASABLE ADDRESS. MOST OF THESE CODES ARE TWO ADDRESS, SPECIFYING THAT THE WORD
000940,000377:                                                                                          	# FOLLOWING THE STORE CODE IS TO BE USED AS AN ADDRESS FROM WHICH TO RE-LOAD MPAC. FOUR OPTIONS ARE AVAILABLE:
000941,000378: 
000942,000379:                                                                                          	#          1. STORE               STORE MPAC. THE E ADDRESS MAY BE INDEXED.
000943,000380:                                                                                          	#          2. STODL               STORE MPAC AND RE-LOAD IT IN DP WITH THE NEXT ADDRESS (THE LOAD MAY BE INDEXED).
000944,000381:                                                                                          	#          3. STOVL               STORE MPAC AND RE-LOAD A VECTOR (AS ABOVE).
000945,000382:                                                                                          	#          4. STCALL              STORE AND DO A CALL (BOTH ADDRESSES MUST BE DIRECT HERE).
000946,000383: 
000947,000384:                                                                                          	#          STODL AND STOVL WILL TAKE FROM THE PUSH-DOWN LIST IF NO LOAD ADDRESS IS GIVEN.
000948,000385: 
000949,000386: 
000950,000387:

001446,000883:                                                                                          	# ARITHMETIC SUBROUTINES REQUIRED IN FIXED-FIXED.
001447,000884: 
001448,000885:                                                                                          	#          1.  DMPSUB     DOUBLE PRECISION MULTIPLY, MULTIPLY THE CONTENTS OF MPAC,+1 BY THE DP WORD WHOSE ADDRESS
001449,000886:                                                                                          	#                         IS IN ADDRWD AND LEAVE A TRIPLE PRECISION RESULT IN MPAC.
001450,000887:                                                                                          	#          2.  ROUNDSUB   ROUND THE TRIPLE PRECISON CONTENTS OF MPAC TO DOUBLE PRECISION.
001451,000888:                                                                                          	#          3.  DOTSUB     TAKE THE DOT PRODUCT OF THE VECTOR IN MPAC AND THE VECTOR WHOSE ADDRESS IS IN ADDRWD
001452,000889:                                                                                          	#                         AND LEAVE THE TRIPLE PRECISION RESULT IN MPAC.
001453,000890:                                                                                          	#          4.  POLY       USING THE CONTENTS OF MPAC AS A DP ARGUMENT, EVALUATE THE POLYNOMIAL WHOSE DEGREE AND
001454,000891:                                                                                          	#                         COEFFICIENTS IMMEDIATELY FOLLOW THE TC POLY INSTRUCTION (SEE ROUTINE FOR DETAILS).

001558,000995:                                                                                          	# DOUBLE PRECISION POLYNOMIAL EVALUATOR
001559,000996: 
001560,000997:                                                                                          	#                                    N        N-1
001561,000998:                                                                                          	#          THIS ROUTINE EVALUATES A X  + A   X    + ... + A  X + A  LEAVING THE DP RESULT IN MPAC ON EXIT.
001562,000999:                                                                                          	#                                  N      N-1              1      0
001563,001000: 
001564,001001:                                                                                          	# THE ROUTINE HAS TWO ENTRIES
001565,001002: 
001566,001003:                                                                                          	#          1. ENTRY THRU POWRSERS. THE COEFFICIENTS MAY BE EITHER IN FIXED OR ERASABLE, THE CALL IS BY
001567,001004:                                                                                          	#             TC POWRSERS, AND THE RETURN IS TO LOC(TC POWRSERS)+1. THE ENTERING DATA MUST BE AS FOLLOWS
001568,001005: 
001569,001006:                                                                                          	#                                         A        SP     LOC-3           ADDRESS FOR REFERENCING COEF TABLE
001570,001007:                                                                                          	#                                         L        SP     N-1             N IS THE DEGREE OF THE POWER SERIES
001571,001008:                                                                                          	#                                         MPAC     DP     X               ARGUMENT
001572,001009: 
001573,001010:                                                                                          	#                                         LOC-2N   DP     A(0)
001574,001011:                                                                                          	#                                                  ...
001575,001012:                                                                                          	#                                         LOC      DP     A(N)
001576,001013: 
001577,001014:                                                                                          	#          2. ENTRY THRU POLY. THE CALL TO POLY AND THE ENTERING DATA MUST BE AS FOLLOWS
001578,001015: 
001579,001016:                                                                                          	#                                         MPAC     DP     X               ARGUMENT
001580,001017: 
001581,001018:                                                                                          	#                                         LOC      TC     POLY
001582,001019:                                                                                          	#                                         LOC+1    SP     N-1
001583,001020:                                                                                          	#                                         LOC+2    DP     A(0)
001584,001021:                                                                                          	#                                                  ...
001585,001022:                                                                                          	#                                         LOC+2N+2 DP     A(N)            RETURN IS TO LOC+2N+4
001586,001023: 
001587,001024:    7175           00006        POWRSERS           EXTEND                                 	#

002533,001970:                                                                                          	#          THE FOLLOWING IS A GENERAL PURPOSE DOUBLE PRECISION DIVISION ROUTINE. IT DIVIDES MPAC BY BUF AND LEAVES
002534,001971:                                                                                          	# THE RESULT IN MPAC. THE FOLLOWING CONDITIONS MUST BE SATISFIED:
002535,001972: 
002536,001973:                                                                                          	#          1.  THE DIVISOR (BUF) MUST BE POSITIVE AND NOT LESS THAN .5.
002537,001974: 
002538,001975:                                                                                          	#          2.  THE DIVIDEND (MPAC) MUST BE POSITIVE WITH THE MAJOR PART OF MPAC STRICTLY LESS THAN THAT OF BUF
002539,001976:                                                                                          	# (A SPECIAL APPROXIMATION, MAXDV, IS USED WHEN THE MAJOR PARTS ARE EQUAL).
002540,001977: 
002541,001978:                                                                                          	#          UNDERSTANDING THAT A/B = Q + S(R/B) WHERE S = 2(-14) AND Q AND R ARE QUOTIENT AND REMAINDER, RESPEC-
002542,001979:                                                                                          	# TIVELY, THE FOLLOWING APPROXIMATION IS OBTAINED BY MULTIPLYING ABOVE AND BELOW BY C - SD AND NEGLECTING TERMS OF
002543,001980:                                                                                          	# ORDER S-SQUARED (POSSIBLY INTRODUCING ERROR INTO THE LOW TWO BITS OF THE RESULT). SIGN AGREEMENT IS UNNECESSARY.
002544,001981: 
002545,001982:                                                                                          	#          A + SB .      (R - QD)                                             A + SB
002546,001983:                                                                                          	#          ------ = Q + S(------) WHERE Q AND R ARE QUOTIENT AND REMAINDER OF ------ RESPECTIVELY.
002547,001984:                                                                                          	#          C + SD        (  C   }                                               C

004262,000097: 01,2566           54000        WAIT2              TS       WAITBANK                      	# BBANK OF CALLING PROGRAM.
WAITLIST.agc:98: Fatal Error: Symbol "TIME3" undefined or offset bad
004263,000098: 01,2567           40000                           CS       TIME3                         	#
004264,000099: 01,2570           62571                           AD       +1                            	# CCS  A  = + 1/4
WAITLIST.agc:100: Fatal Error: Symbol "A" undefined or offset bad
004265,000100: 01,2571           10000                           CCS      A                             	# TEST  1/4 - C(TIME3).  IF POSITIVE,
004266,000101:                                                                                          	# IT MEANS THAT TIME3 OVERFLOW HAS OCCURED PRIOR TO CS  TIME3 AND THAT
004267,000102:                                                                                          	# C(TIME3) = T - T1, INSTEAD OF 1.0 - (T1 - T).  THE FOLLOWING FOUR
004268,000103:                                                                                          	# ORDERS SET C(A) = TD - T1 + 1 IN EITHER CASE.
004269,000104: 
004270,000105: 01,2572           66042                           AD       OCT40001                      	# OVERFLOW HAS OCCURRED.  SET C(A) =
WAITLIST.agc:106: Fatal Error: Symbol "A" undefined or offset bad
004271,000106: 01,2573           40000                           CS       A                             	# T - T1 + 3/4 - 1
004272,000107: 
004273,000108:                                                                                          	# NORMAL CASE (C(A) MINUS) YIELDS SAME C(A)  -(-(1.0-(T1 - T))+1/4)-1
004274,000109: 
004275,000110: 01,2574           62722                           AD       OCT50001                      	#
WAITLIST.agc:111: Fatal Error: Symbol "Q" undefined or offset bad
004276,000111: 01,2575           60000                           AD       Q                             	# RESULT = TD - T1 + 1.
004277,000112: 
WAITLIST.agc:113: Fatal Error: Symbol "A" undefined or offset bad
004278,000113: 01,2576           10000                           CCS      A                             	# TEST TD - T1 + 1
004279,000114: 
WAITLIST.agc:115: Fatal Error: Symbol "LST1" undefined or offset bad
004280,000115: 01,2577           60000                           AD       LST1                          	# IF TD - T1 POS, GO TO WTLST5 WITH
004281,000116: 01,2600           12642                           TCF      WTLST5                        	# C(A) = (TD - T1) + C(LIST1) = TD-T2+1
004282,000117: 
004283,000118: 01,2601           12602                           NOOP                                   	#
WAITLIST.agc:119: Fatal Error: Symbol "Q" undefined or offset bad
004284,000119: 01,2602           40000                           CS       Q                             	#
004285,000120: 
004286,000121:                                                                                          	# NOTE THAT THIS PROGRAM SECTION IS NEVER ENTERED WHEN T-T1 G/E -1,
004287,000122:                                                                                          	# SINCE TD-T1+1 = (TD-T) + (T-T1+1), AND DELTA T = TD-T G/E +1 .  (G/E
004288,000123:                                                                                          	# SYMBOL MEANS GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO).  THUS THERE NEED BE NO CON-
004289,000124:                                                                                          	# CERN OVER A PREVIOUS OR IMMINENT OVEFLOW OF TIME3 HERE.
004290,000125: 
004291,000126: 01,2603           67642                           AD       POS1/2                        	# WHEN TD IS NEXT, FORM QUANTITY
004292,000127: 01,2604           67642                           AD       POS1/2                        	#   1.0 - DELTA T = 1.0 - (TD - T)

004296,000131: 01,2610           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# ZERO INDEX Q.

004391,000226: 
004393,000228: 
004394,000229:                                                                                          	# THE ENTRY TC WTLST2 JUST PRECEDING OCT  N  IS FOR T  LE TD LE T   -1.
004395,000230:                                                                                          	#                                                    N           N+1
004396,000231: 
004397,000232:                                                                                          	# (LE MEANS LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO).  AT ENTRY, C(A) = -(TD - T   + 1)
004398,000233:                                                                                          	#                                                             N+1
004399,000234: 
004400,000235:                                                                                          	# THE LST1 ENTRY -(T   - T +1) IS TO BE REPLACED BY -(TD - T  + 1), AND
004401,000236:                                                                                          	#                   N+1   N                                 N
004402,000237: 
004403,000238:                                                                                          	# THE ENTRY -(T   - TD + 1) IS TO BE INSERTED IMMEDIATELY FOLLOWING.
004404,000239:                                                                                          	#              N+1
004405,000240:

005741,000822:                                                                                          	# Page 181
005742,000823:                                                                                          	# PROGRAM NAME: GPMATRIX          MOD. NO. 0  DATE: OCTOBER 20, 1966
005743,000824: 
005744,000825:                                                                                          	# AUTHOR: JONATHAN D. ADDELSTON (ADAMS ASSOCIATES)
005745,000826: 
005746,000827:                                                                                          	# THIS PROGRAM CALCULATES ALL THE SINGLE-PRECISION MATRIX ELEMENTS WHICH ARE USED BY LEM DAP TO TRANSFORM VECTORS
005747,000828:                                                                                          	# FROM GIMBAL TO PILOT (BODY) AXES AND BACK AGAIN.  THESE ELEMENTS ARE USED EXCLUSIVELY BY BASIC LANGUAGE ROUTINES
005748,000829:                                                                                          	# AND THEREFORE ARE NOT ARRAYED FOR USE BY INTERPRETIVE PROGRAMS.
005749,000830: 
005750,000831:                                                                                          	# CALLING SEQUENCE: GPMATRIX IS ALWAYS EXECUTED 4 TIMES A SECOND BY T4RUPT PROGRAM.  IT IS LISTED EXPLICITLY TWICE
005751,000832:                                                                                          	# IN THE T4JUMP TABLE, BUT IT ALSO OCCURS AFTER RRAUTCHK (TWICE).
005752,000833: 
005753,000834:                                                                                          	# SUBROUTINES CALLED: SPSIN, SPCOS.
005754,000835: 
005755,000836:                                                                                          	# NORMAL EXIT MODE: CONTROL IS ALWAYS TRANSFERRED TO DBSELECT.
005756,000837: 
005757,000838:                                                                                          	# ALARM/ABORT MODE: THERE ARE NO REAL ALARMS OR ABORTS.  HOWEVER, WHEN THE MIDDLE GIMBAL ANGLE NEARS GIMBAL LOCK,
005758,000839:                                                                                          	# A DIVISION BY COS(MG) WILL CAUSE OVERFLOW (I.E. A BAD QUOTIENT).  THIS CONDITION IS PREVENTED BY TESTING COS(MG)
005759,000840:                                                                                          	# AND SUBSTITUTING POSMAX/NEGMAX FOR THE INCALCULABLE QUANTITIES.
005760,000841: 
005761,000842:                                                                                          	# INPUT: CDUX,CDUY,CDUZ.          OUTPUT: M11,M21,M31,M22,M32,MR12,MR13.
005762,000843:                                                                                          	#                                         (ALSO MR22=M22,MR23=M32)        AM DOES NOT DETECT IT.
005763,000844: 
005764,000845:                                                                                          	# *** WARNING ** IT DIES ON DV OVERFLOW.
005765,000846: 
005766,000847:                                                                                          	# AOG = CDUX, AIG = CDUY, AMG = CDUZ: MNEMONIC IS: OIM = XYZ
005767,000848: 
005768,000849:                                                                                          	#    *       *    SIN(MG)        0         1  *
005769,000850:                                                                                          	#    M   =   *    COS(MG)COS(OG) SIN(OG)   0  *
005770,000851:                                                                                          	#     GP     *   -COS(MG)SIN(OG) COS(OG)   0  *
005771,000852: 
005772,000853:                                                                                          	#    *       *  0    COS(OG)/COS(MG)        -SIN(OG)/COS(MG)         *
005773,000854:                                                                                          	#    M   =   *  0    SIN(OG)                 COS(OG)                 *
005774,000855:                                                                                          	#     PG     *  1   -SIN(MG)COS(OG)/COS(MG)  SIN(MG)SIN(OG)/COS(MG)  *
005775,000856: 
T4RUPT_PROGRAM.agc:857: Fatal Error: Symbol "CDUZ" undefined or offset bad

005832,000913:                                                                                          	# THE FOLLOWING SECTION TESTS THE ATTITUDE HOLD BIT TO DETERMINE WHICH DEA
005834,000915:                                                                                          	# PROGRAM NAME: DB SELECT         MOD. NO. 1  DATE: OCTOBER 24, 1966
005835,000916: 
005836,000917:                                                                                          	# AUTHOR: JONATHAN D. ADDELSTON (ADAMS ASSOCIATES)
005837,000918: 
005838,000919:                                                                                          	# THIS PROGRAM SETS THE ERASABLE REGISTER DB TO ONE OF THE THREE VALUES:
005839,000920:                                                                                          	#          1) O.3 DEGREES IF IN ATTITUDE HOLD MODE OR IF IN AUTO WITH THE DEADBAND SELECT BIT OF DAPBOOLS SET
005840,000921:                                                                                          	#             TO MINIMUM.
005841,000922:                                                                                          	#          2) 5.0 DEGREES IF IN AUTO WITH DEADBAND SELECT BIT SET TO MAXIMUM.
005842,000923:                                                                                          	#          3) 1.0 DEGREES IF IN POWERED FLIGHT (ASCENT OR DESCENT) AND OVERRIDING ANY SETTING OF SCSMODE OR THE
005843,000924:                                                                                          	#             DEADBAND SELECT BIT.  (*** SEE COMMENT AFTER CODING. ***)
005844,000925: 
005845,000926:                                                                                          	# ***** NOTICE *****
005846,000927: 
005847,000928:                                                                                          	# THE ABOVE CAPABILTY FULFILLS ALL THE KNOWN DEADBAND REQUIREMENTS FOR AS206, AS208B, AND AS278 (GIVEN THE
005848,000929:                                                                                          	# APPROPRIATE MISSION PROGRAMS).
005849,000930: 
005850,000931:                                                                                          	# (ALSO FOR MANNED FLIGHTS A DSKY ENTRY MUST BE SET UP TO SET THE DEADBAND BITS OF DAPBOOLS. - NOT DONE AS
005851,000932:                                                                                          	# OF 10/24/66.)
005852,000933: 
005853,000934:                                                                                          	# ***** DEADBAND SELECT BIT IS BIT13 OF DAPBOOLS. *****
005854,000935:                                                                                          	#          0: MEANS MINIMUM DEADBAND
005855,000936:                                                                                          	#          1: MEANS MAXIMUM DEADBAND
005856,000937: 
005857,000938:                                                                                          	# CALLING SEQUENCE: CONTROL FALLS THROUGH FROM GPMATRIX. (4 TIMES/SECOND)
005858,000939: 
005859,000940:                                                                                          	# SUBROUTINES CALLED: NONE.
005860,000941: 
005861,000942:                                                                                          	# NORMAL EXIT MODE: CONTROL IS ALWAYS TRANSFERRED TO UP/DOWN.
005862,000943: 
005863,000944:                                                                                          	# ALARM/ABORT MODE: NONE.
005864,000945: 
005865,000946:                                                                                          	# INPUT: BIT13/CHNL11,BIT13/CHNL31,BIT13/DAPBOOLS.  (SPOOKY, ISN'T IT?)
005866,000947: 
005867,000948:                                                                                          	# OUTPUT: DB (SCALED AT PI RADIANS).     (NO DEBRIS EXCEPT A)
005868,000949: 
005869,000950: 12,3620           37643        DBSELECT           CAF      BIT13                         	# ATTITUDE HOLD BIT OF CHANNEL 31
005870,000951: 12,3621           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# 0 MEANS ATTITUDE HOLD
005871,000952: 12,3622           02031                           RAND     31                            	# 1 MEANS EITHER OFF OR AUTO
005872,000953: 12,3623           00006                           EXTEND                                 	#
005873,000954: 12,3624           13633                           BZF      ATTHLDDB                      	# (ATTITUDE HOLD BRANCH)
005874,000955: 
T4RUPT_PROGRAM.agc:956: Fatal Error: Symbol "DAPBOOLS" undefined or offset bad
005875,000956: 12,3625           40000                           CS       DAPBOOLS                      	# DEADBAND SELECT BIT OF DAPBOOLS
005876,000957: 12,3626           77643                           MASK     BIT13                         	# 0 MEANS MINIMUM DEADBAND
T4RUPT_PROGRAM.agc:958: Fatal Error: Symbol "A" undefined or offset bad
005877,000958: 12,3627           10000                           CCS      A                             	# 1 MEANS MAXIMUM DEADBAND
005878,000959: 12,3630           13633                           TCF      ATTHLDDB                      	# (MINIMUM DEADBAND BRANCH)
005879,000960: 
005880,000961: 12,3631           33745                           CAF      DBMAXUM                       	# SET MAXIMUM DEADBAND
005881,000962: 12,3632           13634                           TCF      +2                            	#
005882,000963: 
005883,000964: 12,3633           33747        ATTHLDDB           CAF      DBATTHLD                      	# SET MINUMUM (ATTITUDE HOLD) DEADBAND
T4RUPT_PROGRAM.agc:966: Fatal Error: Symbol "DB" undefined or offset bad
005885,000966: 12,3634           54000                           TS       DB                            	#
005886,000967: 
005887,000968:                                                                                          	# ***** IMPORTANT NOTICE *****
005888,000969: 
005889,000970:                                                                                          	# FOR EFFICIENCY, THE OVERRIDING 1 DEGREE DEADBAND DURING POWERED FLIGHT IS NOT TESTED FOR ABOVE. THE PROGRAM
005890,000971:                                                                                          	# FOLLOWING (I.E. UP/DOWN) PERFORMS THIS FUNCTION AFTER THE APPROPRIATE TESTS. THEREFORE, DB MAY TRANSIENTLY BE
005891,000972:                                                                                          	# INVALID, BUT THE DAP CANNOT USE IT THEN DUE TO T4RUPT MODE.
005892,000973:                                                                                          	# Page 186
005893,000974:                                                                                          	# PROGRAM NAME: UP/DOWN           MOD. NO. 1  DATE: OCTOBER 25, 1966
005894,000975: 
005895,000976:                                                                                          	# AUTHOR: JONATHAN D. ADDELSTON (ADAMS ASSOCIATES)
005896,000977: 
005897,000978:                                                                                          	# THIS PROGRAM MONITORS THE STAGE OF THE LEM AND THE ENGINE ON BIT IN ORDER TO DETERMINE WHEN ASCENT, DESCENT, AND
005898,000979:                                                                                          	# COAST PHASES MUST BE SET UP FOR THE DAP. (DONE 4 TIMES A SECOND.)
005899,000980: 
005900,000981:                                                                                          	# CALLING SEQUENCE: NONE.         SUBROUTINES CALLED: WAITLIST.
005901,000982: 
005902,000983:                                                                                          	# NORMAL EXIT MODE: CONTROL IS ALWAYS TRANSFERRED TO ENDDAPT4.
005903,000984: 
005904,000985:                                                                                          	# ALARM/ABORT MODE: NONE.
005905,000986: 
005906,000987:                                                                                          	# INPUT:BIT2/CHNL30,BIT13/CHNL11,BIT8/DAPBOOLS.
005907,000988: 
005908,000989:                                                                                          	# OUTPUT:  A) ASCENT COAST:
005909,000990:                                                                                          	#                 1) BIT8/DAPBOOLS SET TO ZERO, MEANING COAST.
005910,000991:                                                                                          	#                 2) MINIMPDB AND DBMINIMP SET TO 0.3 DEGREES.
005911,000992:                                                                                          	#          B) ASCENT BURN:
005912,000993:                                                                                          	#                 1) INITIALIZATION PASS:
005913,000994:                                                                                          	#                        I) BIT8/DAPBOOLS SET FROM 0 TO 1, MEANING THAT THE AOSTASK HAS BEEN STARTED UP AND THAT
005914,000995:                                                                                          	#                           INITIALIZATION HAS OCCURRED.
005915,000996:                                                                                          	#                       II) MINIMPDB SET TO -DB.
005916,000997:                                                                                          	#                      III) DBMINIMP SET TO ZERO.
005917,000998:                                                                                          	#                       IV) SUMRATEQ AND SUMRATER ZEROED FOR FIRST TWO SECOND AOSTASK SAMPLE PERIOD.
005918,000999:                                                                                          	#                        V) KCOEFCTR ZEROED TO RECORD INITIAL TIME.
005919,001000:                                                                                          	#                       VI) OMEGAQ AND OMEGAR RECORDED IN OLDWFORQ AND OLDWFORR AS LAST OMEGA VECTOR FOR AOSTASK.
005920,001001:                                                                                          	#                      VII) AOSTASK SET IN WAITLIST FOR TWO SECONDS.
005921,001002:                                                                                          	#                     VIII) DB SET TO DBAUTO.
005922,001003:                                                                                          	#                       IX) ****** CHECKOUT ONLY **** IXXTASK, IYYTASK, AND IZZTASK SET IN WAITLIST FOR TEN MS.
005923,001004:                                                                                          	#                 2) NORMAL PASS VOID.
005924,001005:                                                                                          	#          C) DESCENT COAST:
005925,001006:                                                                                          	#                 1) BIT2/DAPBOOLS SET TO 1, MEANING THAT TRIM GIMBAL CONTROL OF DESCENT IS IMPOSSIBLE SINCE
005926,001007:                                                                                          	#                    DESCENT ENGINE OFF.
005927,001008:                                                                                          	#                 2) AOSQTERM AND AOSRTERM ZEROED.
005928,001009:                                                                                          	#          D) DESCENT BURN:
005929,001010:                                                                                          	#                 1) DB SET TO DBAUTO.
005930,001011:                                                                                          	#                 2) BIT2/DAPBOOLS CANNOT NOW BE ZEROED (EVEN THOUGH THE DESCENT ENGINE IS ON), SINCE IT IS NOT
005931,001012:                                                                                          	#                    NECESSARILY TRUE THAT THIS IMPLIES AN OPERATIVE TRIM GIMBAL SYSTEM.
005932,001013: 
005933,001014: 12,3635           37656        UP/DOWN            CAF      BIT2                          	# STAGE VERIFY BIT OF CHANNEL 30: INVERTED
005934,001015: 12,3636           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# 0 MEANS ASCENT STAGE
005935,001016: 12,3637           02030                           RAND     30                            	# 1 MEANS DESCENT STAGE
T4RUPT_PROGRAM.agc:1017: Fatal Error: Symbol "A" undefined or offset bad
005936,001017: 12,3640           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
005937,001018: 12,3641           13723                           TCF      DESCLEM                       	# (DESCENT STAGE BRANCH)
005938,001019: 
005939,001020: 12,3642           37643        ASCLEM             CAF      BIT13                         	# ENGINE ON BIT OF CHANNEL 11
005940,001021: 12,3643           00006                           EXTEND                                 	# 0 MEANS OFF
005941,001022: 12,3644           02011                           RAND     11                            	# 1 MEANS ON
T4RUPT_PROGRAM.agc:1023: Fatal Error: Symbol "A" undefined or offset bad
005942,001023: 12,3645           10000                           CCS      A                             	#
005944,001025: 12,3646           13656                           TCF      ASCDAP                        	# (ASCENT BURN BRANCH)
005945,001026: 
005946,001027: 12,3647           47650        ASCCOAST           CS       BIT8                          	# SET BIT8 OF DAPBOOLS TO COAST DAP LOGIC

006074,000006:                                                                                          	# Contact:      Hartmuth Gutsche<hgutsche@xplornet.com>.
006075,000007:                                                                                          	# Website:      https://www.ibiblio.org/apollo.
006076,000008:                                                                                          	# Pages:        209-217
006077,000009:                                                                                          	# Mod history:  2016-09-20 JL   Created.
006078,000010:                                                                                          	#               2016-09-21 HG   Initial transcription from scans
006079,000011: 
006080,000012:                                                                                          	# This source code has been transcribed or otherwise adapted from
006081,000013:                                                                                          	# digitized images of a hardcopy from the private collection of 
006082,000014:                                                                                          	# Don Eyles.  The digitization was performed by archive.org.
006083,000015: 
006084,000016:                                                                                          	# Notations on the hardcopy document read, in part:
006085,000017: 
006086,000018:                                                                                          	#       473423A YUL SYSTEM FOR BLK2: REVISION 12 of PROGRAM AURORA BY DAP GROUP
006087,000019:                                                                                          	#       NOV 10, 1966
006088,000020:

006090,000022:                                                                                          	#       date of the program revision or the assembly.]

006093,000025:                                                                                          	# reduction in image quality) are available online at
