006096,000028:                                                                                          	#       https://archive.org/details/aurora00dapg
006097,000029: 
006098,000030:                                                                                          	##Page 209
006099,000031: 07,2000                                           BANK     7                             	#
IMU_COMPENSATION_PACKAGE.agc:32: Fatal Error: Symbol "NBDX" undefined or offset bad
006100,000032: 07,2000                                           EBANK=   NBDX                          	#
006101,000033:                                                                                          	# PROGRAM DESCRIPTION- IMU COMPENSATION (LEM)                             DATE- 30 AUG 66
006102,000034:                                                                                          	# MOD NO- 0                                                               LOG SECTION- IMU COMPENSATION PACKAGE
006103,000035:                                                                                          	# MOD BY- GILBERT                                                         ASSEMBLY- SUNBURST REVISION 13 
006104,000036: 
006105,000037:                                                                                          	# FUNCTIONAL DESCRIPTION
006106,000038:                                                                                          	#       THE IMU COMPENSATION PACKAGE IS DESIGNED TO COMPENSATE FOR PIPA BIAS AND SCALE FACTOR ERROR AND AT THE
006107,000039:                                                                                          	# SAME TIME ACCUMULATE GYRO TORQUING COMMANDS NECESSARY TO COMPENSATE FOR THE ASSOCIATED BIAS AND ACCELERATION-
006108,000040:                                                                                          	# CAUSED GYRO DRIFTS. 1/PIPA MUST BE CALLED AT LEAST EVERY 2.55 SECONDS DUE TO SCALING CONSIDERATIONS.
006109,000041:                                                                                          	# SPECIFICALLY, THE CORRECTION IS
006110,000042: 
006111,000043:                                                                                          	#       PIPA  = (1 + SCALE FACTOR ERROR)PIPA  -  (BIAS)(DELTAT)
006112,000044:                                                                                          	#           C                               I
006113,000045: 
006114,000046:                                                                                          	# WHERE PIPA  IS THE COMPENSATED DATA OBTAINED FROM THE SAMPLED DATA PIPA
006115,000047:                                                                                          	#           C                                                            I
006116,000048: 
006117,000049:                                                                                          	# THE COMPENSATED DATA IS THEN USED TO COMPUTE THE IRIG TORQUING NECESSARY TO CANCEL THE NBD, ADIA, AND ADSRA
006118,000050:                                                                                          	# GYRO COEFFICIENTS.
006119,000051:                                                                                          	# SPECIFICALLY, THE COMPUTATIONS ARE
006120,000052: 
006121,000053:                                                                                          	#       XIRIG     -(ADIAX)(PIPAX ) + (ADSRAX)(PIPAY ) - (NBDX)(DELTAT)  
006122,000054:                                                                                          	#                               C                  C
006123,000055:                                                                                          	#       YIRIG     -(ADIAY)(PIPAY ) + (ADSRAY)(PIPAZ ) - (NBDY)(DELTAT)
006124,000056:                                                                                          	#                               C                  C  
006125,000057:                                                                                          	#       ZIRIG     -(ADIAZ)(PIPAZ ) - (ADSRAZ)(PIPAY ) + (NBDZ)(DELTAT)
006126,000058:                                                                                          	#                               C                  C
006127,000059: 
006128,000060:                                                                                          	# THIS COMPENSATION IS SUMMED INTO THE GCOMP REGISTERS AND WHEN THE MAGNITUDE OF ANY IRIG COMMAND EXCEEDS 2
006129,000061:                                                                                          	# PULSES, THE COMMANDS ARE SENT TO THE GYROS.
006130,000062: 
006131,000063:                                                                                          	# DURING FREE-FALL PHASES OF A FLIGHT NBDX, NBDY, AND NBDZ ARE THE ONLY RELEVANT COEFFICIENTS. THESE BIAS TERMS
006132,000064:                                                                                          	# WILL BE INTEGRATED BY BY ROUTINE NBDONLY APPROXIMATELY EVERY 81.93 SECONDS FOLLOWING AN EXECUTIVE CALL BY THE DUMMY
006133,000065:                                                                                          	# TASK OF THE WAITLIST PROGRAM. NBDONLY IS ENABLED WHEN BIT 15 OF FLAGWRD2 IS SET TO INDICATE FREE-FALL. DURING
006134,000066:                                                                                          	# THIS TIME 1/PIPA IS NOT CALLED.
006135,000067: 
006136,000068:                                                                                          	# LASTBIAS IS CALLED VIA EXECUTIVE WHEN MAKING THE TRANSITION FROM-FALL TO A PIPA READING MODE. THE NBD TERMS
006137,000069:                                                                                          	# ARE COMPENSATED FOR FROM THE LAST NBDONLY CALL UP TO PIPA ZEROING. PREREAD WILL THEN ENABLE 1/PIPA AT ITS
006138,000070:                                                                                          	# REGULAR INTERVAL. THE DRIFT FLAG MUST BE DOWN JUST PRIOR TO LASTBIAS. GYROCOMPASS NEVER CALLS LASTBIAS.
006139,000071: 
006140,000072:                                                                                          	# SCALING CONSIDERATIONS
006141,000073:                                                                                          	#                            UNITS              MAX. VALUE     INTERNAL UNITS AND SCALING
006142,000074: 
006143,000075:                                                                                          	#        PIPA BIAS           (CM)/(SEC)(SEC)    3.125          (PIPA PULSES)/(CS) X 2(-5) 
006144,000076:                                                                                          	#        PIPA SCALE FACTOR   P.P.M.             1953.125       (PPM) X 2(-9)
006145,000077:                                                                                          	#        NBD                 MERU               128.74604      (GYRO PULSES)/(CS) X 2(-5) 
006146,000078:                                                                                          	#        ADIA                (MERU)/(G)         630.36633      (GYRO PULSES)/(PIPA PULSE) X 2(-6)
006147,000079:                                                                                          	#        ADSRA               (MERU)/(G)         630.36633      (GYRO PULSES)/(PIPA PULSE) X 2(-6)
006148,000080: 
006149,000081:                                                                                          	##Page 210
006150,000082:                                                                                          	# CONVERSION TABLE
006151,000083:                                                                                          	#       1 PIPA PULSE = 1.00 (CM)/(SEC)(SEC)          1 ERU = 7.29209817 X 10(-5) (RAD)/(SEC)
006152,000084:                                                                                          	#       1 ERU = 15.04104488 (ARCSEC)/(SEC)           1 (CM)/(SEC)(SEC) = .01 (PIPA PULSES)/(CS)
006153,000085:                                                                                          	#       1 GYRO PULSE = .61798096 (ARCSEC)            1 MERU = .0024272592 (GYRO PULSES)/(CS)
006154,000086:                                                                                          	#       1 g = 979.24 (CM)/(SEC)(SEC)                 1 (MERU)/(G) = .000144787174 (GYRO PULSES)/(PIPA PULSE)
006155,000087: 
006156,000088:                                                                                          	# REFERENCES
006157,000089:                                                                                          	#       AGC PROGRAMMING MEMO NO. 12, I.S.S. MEMO NO. 247, I.S.S. MEMO NO 328, I.S.S. MEMO NO. 339
006158,000090: 
006159,000091:                                                                                          	# CALLING SEQUENCE 
006160,000092:                                                                                          	#       L      TC     BANKALL
006161,000093:                                                                                          	#       L+1    CADR   1/PIPA
006162,000094:                                                                                          	#       L+2                       RETURNS HERE
006163,000095: 
006164,000096:                                                                                          	# NORMAL EXIT MODES
006165,000097:                                                                                          	#       AT L+2 OF CALLING SEQUENCE
006166,000098: 
006167,000099:                                                                                          	# ALARM OR ABORT MODES
006168,000100:                                                                                          	#       ENDOFJOB
006169,000101: 
006170,000102:                                                                                          	# ERASABLE INITIALIZATION REQUIRED (CONSECUTIVE LOCATIONS)
006171,000103:                                                                                          	#       PBIASX    PIPAX BIAS
006172,000104:                                                                                          	#       PIPASCFX  PIPAX SCALE FACTOR ERROR
006173,000105:                                                                                          	#       PBIASY    PIPAY BIAS
006174,000106:                                                                                          	#       PIPASCFY  PIPAY SCALE FACTOR ERROR
006175,000107:                                                                                          	#       PBIASZ    PIPAZ BIAS
006176,000108:                                                                                          	#       PIPASCFZ  PIPAZ SCALE FACTOR ERROR
006177,000109:                                                                                          	#       NBDX      X IRIG BIAS DRIFT
006178,000110:                                                                                          	#       NBDY      Y IRIG BIAS DRIFT
006179,000111:                                                                                          	#       NDBZ      Z IRIG BIAS DRIFT
006180,000112:                                                                                          	#       ADIAX     IRIG ACCELERATION SENSITIVE DRIFT ALONG THE X INPUT AXIS  
006181,000113:                                                                                          	#       ADIAY     IRIG ACCELERATION SENSITIVE DRIFT ALONG THE Y INPUT AXIS 
006182,000114:                                                                                          	#       ADIAZ     IRIG ACCELERATION SENSITIVE DRIFT ALONG THE Z INPUT AXIS
006183,000115:                                                                                          	#       ADSRAX    IRIG ACCELERATION SENSITIVE DRIFT ALONG THE X SPIN REFERENCE AXIS      
006184,000116:                                                                                          	#       ADSRAY    IRIG ACCELERATION SENSITIVE DRIFT ALONG THE Y SPIN REFERENCE AXIS  
006185,000117:                                                                                          	#       ADSRAZ    IRIG ACCELERATION SENSITIVE DRIFT ALONG THE Z SPIN REFERENCE AXIS
006186,000118:                                                                                          	#       GCOMP     GYRO COMPENSATION PULSES (SET = ZERO FOR 1ST PASS)
006187,000119: 
006188,000120:                                                                                          	# INPUT
006189,000121:                                                                                          	#       1/PIPADT - DELTA TIME SCALED AT (CS) X 2(+8)
006190,000122:                                                                                          	#       DELVX, DELVY, DELVZ - PIPA READINGS IN THE MAJOR PARTS - MINOR PARTS IRRELEVANT 
006191,000123: 
006192,000124:                                                                                          	# OUTPUT
006193,000125:                                                                                          	#       DELVX, DELVY, DELVZ - PIPA COUNTS SCALED 2(+14) COMPENSATED FOR PIPA BIAS AND SCALE FACTOR ERROR
006194,000126:                                                                                          	#       GCOMP - 3 DP LOCATIONS CONTAINING GYRO PULSES TO COMPENSATE FOR NBD, ADIA, AND ADSRA COEFFICIENTS
006195,000127: 
006196,000128:                                                                                          	# DEBRIS
006197,000129:                                                                                          	#       CENTRALS - A,L,Q
006198,000130:                                                                                          	#       OTHER - BUF - BUF +2, VBUF - VBUF +2, GCOMPSW
006199,000131: 
006200,000132:                                                                                          	##Page 211
006201,000133: 07,2000           32233        1/PIPA             CAF      LGCOMP                        	# SAVE EBANK OF CALLING PROGRAM

006743,000118: 
006744,000119:                                                                                          	# UPACT IS TURNED OFF BY VBRELDSP, ALSO BY ERROR LIGHT RESET.       
006746,000121:                                                                                          	# THE RECEPTION OF A BAD CODE BY UPLINK LOCKS OUT FURTHER UPLINK ACTIVITY
006747,000122:                                                                                          	# BY PLACING A 1 INTO BIT1 OF UPLOCK. BIT9 (ALONG WITH BIT11) OF TMKEYBUF
006748,000123:                                                                                          	# IS SET TO 1 TO SEND AN INDICATION OF THIS SITUATION DOWN THE DOWNLINK.
006749,000124:                                                                                          	# THE UPLINK INTERLOCK IS ALLOWED WHEN AN ERROR LIGHT RESET CODE IS SENT
006750,000125:                                                                                          	# UP THE UPLINK, OR WHEN A FRESH START IS PERFORMED.
006751,000126: 
006752,000127: 07,2502                                           EQUALS                                 	#
